Internship Programs 


Discovery Communications provides students with various paid learning opportunities to experience firsthand what it is like to work for the leader in global entertainment. Students gain valuable industry knowledge through shadowing, networking opportunities and hands-on training. Discovery’s Internship Programs serve as a vital source for building a qualified candidate pool for permanent positions.
Search all of our open internship opportunities.
 United States

What could be cooler than interning at the home of Shark Week, the place where the Cake Boss creates his masterpieces or where you can see the world’s cutest puppies playing “ruff” during Puppy Bowl?
Through the Discovery INternship Program, INterns have the unique opportunity to learn about the entertainment and media industry from the leader in global entertainment through a paid, 12 week internship. We hire curious, creative, passionate individuals across many of our offices in the United States.
Discovery INterns will be presented with exclusive hands-on learning experiences, mentorship, executive speakers and networking sessions. INterns will also have the opportunity to learn about Discovery’s mission, values, culture and commitment to quality programming, products and services. In turn, INterns will be able to showcase their unique talents, cultivate their skills and most importantly, have fun while doing it. Discovery INterns are natural curiosity seekers who think creatively to succeed at any task put in front them. They possess ambition and tenacity that makes them an outstanding and important part of the company. Are you curious? See for yourself what it’s like to be a #DiscoveryINtern on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook.
Discovery offers internship positions across all departments, not just media-centric majors. Intern-seeking departments include:
Accounting & Finance, Ad Sales, Business & Legal Affairs, Communications & PR, Creative & Design, Digital Media, Education, Engineering & Media Technology, Human Resources, Insights & Research, IT, Marketing, Production, Social Media, Talent Casting, TV Development, TV Programming & Scheduling
For updates on the Discovery INternship Program, like our Facebook page, and search #DiscoveryINtern on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook for an inside look at what it’s like to intern in Discovery’s collaborative, creative atmosphere. 






Our INterns get just a little excited for Shark Week.
No two days are alike at Discovery, you never know who may stop by and chat with the INterns. 
Not only do you get an amazing INternship experience at Discovery, you get some amazing friends too!
Our INterns come from colleges all over the nation! 
Our INternships offer hands on experience, turning INternships into dream jobs. 
Discovery INterns in Silver Spring, Maryland at orientation.
It may be a bad week to be a seal, but it is always a great week to be a Discovery Intern in Chicago.
TLC INterns enjoying their summer at our Silver Spring, MD Headquarters.
Discovery INterns can stand up to any “hairy” situation.
Discovery INterns give back at Discover Your Impact Day, Discovery’s annual day of global employee volunteerism.
All smiles in our Los Angeles office for this INtern help to make cards for Discovery’s Impact Day, a day of global volunteerism.
Shark Week is the most wonderful week of the year in our Los Angeles office. 
INterns or FINterns? 
Chompie Jr. greeted our INterns at the John Hendricks Innovation Awards celebrating employee achievement. 
Discovery INterns create a community amongst each other that lasts long beyond their internship.
Shark Week and Say Yes to the Dress collide for these INterns.







Internship FAQ

What departments do you offer INternships in?

Discovery offers internship positions across all departments, not just media-centric majors. Intern-seeking departments include:

Accounting & Finance
Ad Sales
Business & Legal Affairs
Communications & PR
Creative & Design
Digital Media
Education
Engineering & Media Technology
Human Resources
Insights & Research
IT
Marketing
Production
Social Media
Talent Casting
TV Development
TV Programming & Scheduling




Where do you offer INternships?

INternships are offered in multiple offices across the U.S. Please check our open opportunities to see where we are offering positions that semester.



When do you offer INternships?

Discovery has internships during the spring and summer semesters. We do not offer fall internships at this time.



Where can I find more information?

For updates on the Discovery INternship Program, like our Facebook page, and search #DiscoveryINtern on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook for an inside look at what it’s like to intern in Discovery’s collaborative, creative atmosphere.



Who Should Apply?

Students must be a Junior, Senior, or Graduate Student enrolled full time at an accredited college or university to participate in our INternship program. Proof of enrollment will be required if selected. Students must also have the legal right to work in the United States and have a 3.0 GPA.
Unfortunately recent graduates are not eligible for the program.



When do I apply?

We’re live! Our Summer 2017 opportunities have been posted. The deadline to apply is March 31st, after that we cannot guarantee your application will be reviewed for the position.
For our spring semester check back in September 2017.



Housing?

If selected for an INternship you will be responsible for securing your own housing.



When will I hear back?

Due to the high number of applications we receive each semester we are unable to respond to individual requests for status updates. You may be contacted for an interview any time between September and December for our spring semester and February through April for our summer semester.




United Kingdom

What could be cooler than interning with the Number 1 Pay TV Programmer in the world!? The home of Eurosport, and soon to be of the Olympic Games! The creative hub for the creators of Shark Week, the place where our Cake Boss creates his masterpieces and David Emmanuel has all of those fabulous women saying “Yes to the Dress”.
Through the Discovery INternship Program, INterns have the unique opportunity to learn about the entertainment and media industry from the leader in global entertainment through a paid, 12 week or 12 month internship. We hire curious, creative, passionate individuals across many of our offices in the UK.
Discovery INterns are presented with exclusive hands-on learning experiences, mentorship, executive speaker and networking sessions. You will also have the opportunity to learn about Discovery’s mission, values, culture and commitment to quality programming, products and services. In turn, you will be able to showcase your unique talents, cultivate their skills and most importantly, have fun while doing it. Discovery INterns are natural curiosity seekers who think creatively to succeed at any task put in front them. They possess ambition and tenacity that makes them an outstanding and important part of the company. Are you curious? See for yourself what it’s like to get #Discovered and become a #DiscoveryINtern on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook.
For updates on the Discovery INternship Program, search #DiscoveryINtern on Instagram, Twitter and Facebook for an inside look at what it’s like to intern in Discovery’s collaborative, creative atmosphere!






Are you IN?



Our INterns & Grads had the amazing opportunity to hang out Marjorie Kaplan, President of Content for Discovery Networks International, learning the ropes of creating content & useful tips of the trade! 







Internship FAQ

What departments do you offer INternships in?

Discovery offers internship positions across all departments, not just media-centric majors. Intern-seeking departments include:

Accounting & Finance
Ad Sales
Brand Partnerships
Business & Legal Affairs
Communications & PR
Creative & Design
Digital Media
Engineering & Media Technology
Eurosport
Human Resources
Insights & Research
IT& Facilities
Marketing
Production
TV Programming & Scheduling




Where do you offer INternships?

INternships are offered within our Chiswick Park and Feltham (Eurosport) offices. Please check our open opportunities to see where we are offering positions within our next intake.



When do you offer INternships?

All UK Discovery and Eurosport internships start in July each year. They run for a 12 week or 12 month period from that date, dependent on which opportunity you secure. 



Where can I find more information?

All UK Discovery and Eurosport internship opportunities are advertised on the related careers sites – if you visit the corporate pages and click through to our careers links you’ll find them there!  



Who Should Apply?

Students in their sandwich year of university are our main source of candidates for this programme. However, there are certain business areas that are open to considering talented and creative individuals without a degree – so if you are curious, creative, passionate, and feel you can add value to our business, get in touch! 



When do I apply?

Keep an eye out for application launch in Q4 of each year. 



Housing?

If selected for an INternship you will be responsible for securing your own housing. But we do have some information that we can send your way – in addition to connecting you with other Interns who may be open to seeking housing in groups. 



When will I hear back?

Due to the high number of applications we receive each year we are unable to respond to individual requests for status updates. You may be contacted for an interview any time between October and December for our intake in July of the following year.




Germany

The Discovery Germany Intern Program, based out of the Munich office, is a paid learning experience targeting current university students or upcoming graduates to gain valuable industry knowledge and skills through hands-on training, work shadowing, project management and
networking opportunities. 

Italy

The Discovery Italy Internship Program is a paid learning experience targeting current university students or upcoming graduates to gain valuable industry knowledge and skills. Internships run for 6 months and are based in our offices in Milan and Rome. We also have a specific internship program, focused on our Advertising Sales team. 

Latin America

Coming Soon!









