Discovery Communications, Inc. is an American global mass media and entertainment company based in Silver Spring, Maryland. The company started as a single channel in 1985, The Discovery Channel.
DCI both produces original television programming and acquires content from producers worldwide. The company's non-fiction, lifestyle, sports and kids programming is offered through pay-TV and free-to-air networks, among them Discovery Channel, TLC, Investigation Discovery, Animal Planet, OWN: Oprah Winfrey Network, Science, Velocity, Eurosport as well as direct-to-consumer digital offerings including Discovery’s GO suite of apps, Discovery Kids Play and Eurosport Player.[4][5]
Discovery Communications partnered with the World Wildlife Fund to fund conservation of 1 million acres of land for Tigers in Bhutan and India and to help double the world's wild tiger population through Project C.A.T. (Conserving Acres for Tigers) in October 2016.[6]



