Discovery Times






 


The Science Channel
Product Announcement from Discovery Communications, Inc.











The Science Channel is the ultimate source for entertaining specials and up-to-the-minute science news. In 37 million homes, The Science Channel takes viewers down to the molten core beneath the Earth's surface and to the outer edges of the solar system to explain how the universe works. The network also continues to be the source for up-to-the-minute space programming, with live coverage of the space shuttle's return to space and an exclusive and emotional documentary of Columbia's tragic final mission based on footage shot by one of its lost astronauts. 
The Science Channel remains a major source for science-related television programming through ongoing partnerships with some of the world's leading scientific organizations, including the American Association for the Advancement of Science, the Woods Hole Oceanographic Institute, Scientific American, National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) and the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA). These special partnerships give the network exclusive access to some of the most intriguing scientific stories of the day.








